The paper discusses a method for distributed training of neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on fully connected, feed-forward neural networks, which suggests a focus on deep learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the paper deals with distributed training. The paper also mentions real-world speech recognition and product recommendation applications, which suggests a focus on natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), respectively. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of stochastic gradient descent (SGD), which is a common optimization algorithm used in neural networks, suggesting a focus on neural networks and optimization, and thus cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category.
